  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Pamoja kwa mafanikio: Working together for prosperous livelihoods</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">- Strengthen relationship between KDCU and RPCS and other stakeholders in the coffee value chain.
- Strengthen management of financial operations of KDCU and RPCS. 
- Put in place extension infrastructure. 
- Establish ICT platform for data collection and extension support. 
- Develop market intelligence on coffee. 
- Promote KDCU to potential buyers and service providers. 
- Organizing farmers into small groups. 
- Provide extension outreach to farmers related to climate smart beans and coffee production and post-harvest handling. 
- Promote entrepreneurial knowledge and skills to farmers on diversification of the livelihoods strategies.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Coffee Farmers</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project will contribute to increasing resilience of the target farmers to coffee price volatility and a changing climate with the strategic objective that farmers in Karagwe and Kyerwa districts are resilient to coffee price volatility and a changing climate. This objective will be achieved through:
Outcome 1: Targeted  farmers&apos; organizations operate viable businesses
Output 1.1: Targeted farmers&apos; organizations provide quality services
Output 1.2: Targeted farmers&apos; organizations have effective and efficient business operations
Output 1.3:Targeted farmers&apos; organizations provide quality services
Outcome 2: Targeted smallholder coffees farmers have diversified their income sources
Output 2.1: Targeted farmers implement sound, diversified agriculture to respond to variable markets and climate
Output 2.2: Targeted farmers invest in and track their production and marketing activities.</narrative>
  </description>
